questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;You are given two statements and two conclusions. Choose the correct comment about the conclusions from the options given below.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statement:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All forests are trees.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some trees are lions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conclusion:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. Some lions are forests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II. No lion is forests.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The least possible Venn diagram for the given statements is as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/02/F2_PoojaS_Madhuri_04.02.2022_D1.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 111px; height: 81px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. Some lions are forests&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; False (As there is no direct relationship is given between lions and forests)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II. No lion is forests&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr;&amp;nbsp;False (As there is no direct relationship is given between lions and forests)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Conclusions I and II are complementary to each other.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Either conclusion I or conclusion II follows&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For Either and or conditions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. The elements are the same in both the conclusions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II. One conclusion is positive and one is negative.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;III. Individually both the conclusions must be wrong.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img height=&quot;372&quot; src=&quot;https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/aa-rJ_gr7OrGJtS7_tGLSv76nk03ZLmrcNHdYEgM8ZScjZNQRhGyjXTyWJy6vmE6IxoAVKos2yZw47vbwfzYWOuIis03lTRXLUgZV5lS-S0Ny_EPtmGqsNSnqoHjg27T20hZAVbh=s1600&quot; style=&quot;white-space: pre-wrap; margin-left: 0px; margin-top: 0px;&quot; width=&quot;347&quot; /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Three Statements are given followed by two conclusions numbered I and II. Assuming the statements to be true, even if they seem to be at variance with commonly known facts, decide which of the conclusions logically follow(s) from the&amp;nbsp;statements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statement I: &lt;/strong&gt;All bats are balls.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statement II: &lt;/strong&gt;All balls are badmintons.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statement III: &lt;/strong&gt;All badmintons are wickets.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conclusion I:&lt;/strong&gt; All bats are wickets.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conclusion II:&lt;/strong&gt; Some badmintons are bats.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The given statements are-&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Statement I:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;All bats are balls.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Statement II:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;All balls are badmintons.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Statement III:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;All badmintons are wickets.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The least possible Venn Diagram is as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/25/12/Task%20Id%201960%20Daman%20%2816%29.png&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41); width: 300px; height: 295px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Conclusion I:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;All bats are wickets.&amp;rArr; &lt;strong&gt;True&lt;/strong&gt;. (All bats are balls and all balls are wickets. So, all bats are wickets as well.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Conclusion II:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;Some badmintons are bats. &lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;True&lt;/strong&gt;. (All bats are balls and all balls are badmintons. So, some badmintons are bats.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, both conclusions I and II follow.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;In the following question below are given some statements followed by some conclusions. Taking the given statements to be true even if they seem to be at variance from commonly known facts, read all the conclusions and then decide which of the given conclusion logically follows the given statements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. All stars are blue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II. All blue are white.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. All&amp;nbsp;stars are white.&lt;/p&gt;
II. Some stars are not white.

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The least possible Venn diagram for the given statement is as follows,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/19/02/2%20FEB%202019_34.PNG&quot; style=&quot;width: 186px; height: 182px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. All&amp;nbsp;stars are white &amp;rarr; definitely true.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II. Some stars are not white &amp;rarr; definitely false.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, only conclusion I follows.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;In the following question below some statements are given followed by some conclusions. Taking the given statements to be true even if they seem to be at variance from commonly known facts, read all the conclusions and then decide which of the given conclusions logically follows the given statements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Statements :&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All birds are human.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All birds are animal.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Conclusions :&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. Some animal are human.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II. All animal are human.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The least possible Venn diagram for the given statements will be :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/quesImage5377.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conclusions :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. Some animal are human&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; True (As all birds are animal and also all birds are human, so definitely, some animals are human in which birds are the common part).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II. All animal are human&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; False (Some animals are human is definite but all animals being human is just a probability and not definite).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Only conclusion I follows&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Two statements are given, followed by two conclusions numbered I and II. Assuming the statements to be true, even if they seem to be at variance with commonly known facts, decide which of the conclusions logically follow(s) from the statements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some coins are notes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some notes are bills.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. No coin is a bill.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II. All notes being coins is a possibility.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Explanation:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;The least possible Venn diagram of the given statement is:&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/12/F1_Himanshu__SSC_11-12-22_D55.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 259px; height: 61px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;I. No coin is a bill&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; False(It is possible but not definite)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;II. All notes being coins is a possibility&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; True(As there is no negative definite relation is mentioned between Notes and Coins, hence the possibility of all will be true.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Only conclusion II follows&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Option 3&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The statements below are followed by two conclusions labeled I and II. Assuming that the information in the statements is true, even if it appears at variance with generally established facts, decide which conclusion (s logically and definitely follow(s from the information given in the statements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;1) All hens are lions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;2) All lions are cats.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conclusion:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;I. All cats are hens.&lt;/p&gt;
II. Some cats are hens.

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The least possible venn diagram is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/09/F1_Resham.R_31-08-2020_Savita_D31.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;I. All cats are hens. &amp;rarr; False&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;It is possible but not definite. As there is no condition in given statements that &lt;strong&gt;prevents&lt;/strong&gt; all cats&amp;nbsp;to be hens.&amp;nbsp;Also, there is no condition in given statements that&lt;strong&gt; ensures &lt;/strong&gt;that all cats are hens.&amp;nbsp;Hence, &amp;quot;All cats are hens&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;All cats are not hens&amp;quot; both cases are possible.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Possibility of&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;All cats are hens&amp;quot; where&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;all given statements are satisfied&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/quesImage1565.png&quot; style=&quot;height: 152px; width: 150px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Possibility of&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;All cats are not hens&amp;quot; where&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;all given statements are satisfied&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/09/F1_Resham.R_31-08-2020_Savita_D31.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;When a conclusion case is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;only a possibility but not definite&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, we consider such conclusions as &lt;strong&gt;False&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
Hence, &amp;quot;All cats are hens&amp;quot; is a false conclusion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;II. Some cats are hens. &amp;rarr; True&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;As &amp;#39;All hens are lions&amp;#39; and &amp;#39;All lions are cats&amp;#39;. So, some cats are &lt;strong&gt;definitely&lt;/strong&gt; hens.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, only conclusion II follows.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Read the given statements and conclusions carefully. Assuming that the information given in the statements is true, even if it appears to be at variance with commonly known facts, decide which of the given conclusions logically follow(s) from the statements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. No rose is a hibiscus.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. Some hibiscuses are lotuses.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. No rose is a lotus.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II. Some lotuses are not roses.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;Given:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Statements:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;1. No rose is a hibiscus.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;2. Some hibiscuses are lotuses.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The least possible Venn diagram for the given statement is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/23/03/F1_Madhuri_Railways_24.03.2023_D22.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 270px; height: 51px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

